
#1 scp DIRECTORY FROM Remote To local (DOWNLOAD a DIRECTORY)

     scp -r username@hostname:/path/to/file /path/to/destination
     scp -r tomgdow@tomgdow.com:/home/tomgdow/rubyMine_admin_licence . # folder from Digital ocean to Windows PC
     scp -r  tomgdow@tomgdow.com:/home/thomas/Downloads/*.pdf .

  Notes
     to get address of remote machine, run
     hostname -I  # on that machine

#2 scp FILE FROM Remote to local  (DOWNLOAD a FILE)
      
    scp your_username@remotehost.edu:foobar.txt /some/local/directory 

#3 scp DIRECTORY TO remote from local (UPLOAD a DIRECTORY)

    scp -r foo your_username@remotehost.edu:/some/remote/directory/bar 

  Notes

#4 scp file To remote from local (UPLOAD a FILE) 

    scp -r /path/to/file username@hostname:/path/to/destination

  Notes

References

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11304895/how-to-scp-a-folder-from-remote-to-local
